Text.LocalizedString: Good to know, thank you Hunter.

...
You’re right.

Text.LocalizedString: *This strange and secretive organization, what are their motives? How is my mom wrapped up in all this? *

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: ...: "*Whatever the case, when I awaken i..."

Text.LocalizedString: *Whatever the case, when I awaken in the morning, I barely feel rested, and in the afternoon I make my way over to the warehouse.*

Text.LocalizedString: Let’s do this.

Text.LocalizedString: *Our second evening in the warehouse was more gruelling than the last. It’s starting to take its toll on me, I think. We get home exhausted.*

Text.LocalizedString: Please tell me that’s the last time we’re going in there.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Janet: "For one, we don’t know where [Act1V..."

...
I don’t know if it’s safe for us to do that.

Text.LocalizedString: These guys, this Echelon Institute, they seem pretty well connected. To have the firepower they do in there… they must know people in high places.

Text.LocalizedString: Janet-

Text.LocalizedString: It was completely deserved. If this Echelon Institute has the power to get those weapons in there, they certainly have the power to arrest us for breaking and entering, and assault, regardless of their wrongdoings.

Text.LocalizedString: Okay, so what do we do now?

Text.LocalizedString: Let’s take stock of what we found.

Text.LocalizedString: It’s just this one memo.

Text.LocalizedString: I looked it over, it’s more than just a memo. This keeps coming up.

Text.LocalizedString: Operation 8450. Whatever it is, it’s important to them.

Text.LocalizedString: I- I can’t have this argument right now. [Act1Variables.player]?

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Player: "Hunter, you’re out of line, but let..."

Text.LocalizedString: Hunter, you’re out of line, but let’s move on.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Player: "I kind of agree, Hunter, but let’s..."

Text.LocalizedString: I kind of agree, Hunter, but let’s stay on track.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Hunter: "Wow, okay. Yeah let’s go on."

Text.LocalizedString: Wow, okay. Yeah let’s go on.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Janet: "Thank you."

Text.LocalizedString: Thank you.

Text.LocalizedString: Anyway, there’s definitely a lot going on at the Echelon Institute that we don’t fully understand.

Text.LocalizedString: We’ve got a few documents here.

Text.LocalizedString: There are a few things in here I find concerning. First there’s this Operation 8450, which we’ve seen a few times now.

Text.LocalizedString: It sounds like it’s pretty unpopular?

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Janet: "Unpopular but important to them. An..."

Text.LocalizedString:
Unpopular but important to them. And it seems to be closely linked to anti-magic efforts. And it sounds like it’s the one policy proposal they’re comfortable being public about.
They want people to think magic is unnatural and dangerous.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Hunter: "I think we hit the motherlode. Look..."

Text.LocalizedString: I think we hit the motherlode. Look at all these documents.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Janet: "Yes, there’s quite a bit to parse t..."

Text.LocalizedString: Yes, there’s quite a bit to parse through in here. Mechs to suppress magic users, stripping of rights for magic users… this is some dystopian shit.

Text.LocalizedString: What’s this ‘Operation 8450’ that keeps coming up?

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Janet: "I’m not certain, but whatever it is..."

Text.LocalizedString: I’m not certain, but whatever it is, it’s important.

Text.LocalizedString: And unpopular, it looks like.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Janet: "Yes, and closely linked to their an..."

Text.LocalizedString: Yes, and closely linked to their anti-magic efforts. It sounds like this is the one aspect of their project that they think is popular. They’re banking on people fearing magic as unnatural and dangerous.

Text.LocalizedString: So what do we do?

Text.LocalizedString: I’m thinking we need to go back. Even if we don’t figure out what they’re doing, we need to find [Act1Variables.player]’s mom.

...
Okay, we go back one more time. But that’s it. Things are getting dangerous.

...
No, I’ll go with you guys.

Text.LocalizedString: Good. Now let’s let [Act1Variables.player] get some rest.

Text.LocalizedString: *I bid Janet and Hunter good night, and they head home.*

Text.LocalizedString: *After yet another night of restless sleep, and a listless Sunday spent waiting for the evening, it is eventually time for me to head down to the warehouse. I meet Janet and Hunter there and wordlessly- our moods grim- we enter the warehouse for the last time.*

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Player: "Oh my god, that was… something else..."

Text.LocalizedString: Oh my god, that was… something else.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Hunter: "We cannot go back again. Security i..."

Text.LocalizedString: We cannot go back again. Security is just too tight now.

Text.LocalizedString: It’s all good my friends, because we walked out of there with the golden ticket.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Hunter: "Oh?"

Text.LocalizedString: Oh?

Text.LocalizedString: This memo, it says they’re moving everything to their office in the business district.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Player: "Do we know where that is?"

Text.LocalizedString: Do we know where that is?

Text.LocalizedString: Not at this exact moment, but if you give me a couple days I can figure it out. I’ll know in time for us to hit it next weekend.

Text.LocalizedString: Hit it?

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Janet: "Yeah, breaking in, bozo."

Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, breaking in, bozo.

Text.LocalizedString: Guys, I think this is going too far.

Text.LocalizedString: Too far? Hunter, they took [Act1Variables.player]'s mom!

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Hunter: "We don’t know that. Not for sure. A..."

Text.LocalizedString: We don’t know that. Not for sure. And, I don’t know, they seem kinda just like, concerned citizens.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Janet: "I’m sorry, do ‘concerned citizens’..."

Text.LocalizedString: I’m sorry, do ‘concerned citizens’ normally own military grade firepower?

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Player: "Guys-"

Text.LocalizedString: Guys-

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Hunter: "Janet you’ve basically bullied me i..."

Text.LocalizedString: Janet you’ve basically bullied me into going along with your crimes this whole weekend.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Janet: "Look at what we know about the Eche..."

Text.LocalizedString: Look at what we know about the Echelon Institute’s agenda! They want to curtail the rights of people with magical abilities.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Hunter: "If what they’re doing is wrong, the..."

Text.LocalizedString: If what they’re doing is wrong, the law would stop them. We can’t just go around the law because we feel like it!

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Janet: "The law is never wrong? The law is..."

Text.LocalizedString: The law is never wrong? The law is never slow to act? Get your head out of the sand, Hunter.

Text.LocalizedString: GUYS!

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Janet: "Sorry [Act1Variables.player]."

Text.LocalizedString: Sorry [Act1Variables.player].

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Hunter: "Mm, yeah, sorry."

Text.LocalizedString: Mm, yeah, sorry.

Text.LocalizedString: Look, I know you both have some strong feelings, but the fact of the matter is my mom is still missing.

Text.LocalizedString:
And I’m inclined to agree with Janet. Beyond my mom being kidnapped, I feel like we have to at least learn more about the Echelon Institute.
We owe it to everyone to try to understand what they’re doing.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Player: "I'm inclined to agree with Hunter,..."

Text.LocalizedString: I'm inclined to agree with Hunter, and it’s definitely not our place to play the law, but right now the law isn’t doing anything to find my mom.

Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad you agree, [Act1Variables.player].

Text.LocalizedString: If you’re dead-set on this, [Act1Variables.player], then I guess I’m with you, at least for a little bit longer.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Player: "So Hunter, I hope you understand th..."

Text.LocalizedString: So Hunter, I hope you understand that we do need to at least get a more solid lead on where my mom is.

Text.LocalizedString:
...
Okay, I understand [Act1Variables.player]. I’m with you, at least for a little while longer.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Janet: "Thank you, Hunter. That’s mature of..."

Text.LocalizedString: Thank you, Hunter. That’s mature of you.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Player: "Well, if we can all keep our temper..."

Text.LocalizedString: Well, if we can all keep our tempers, I think we’re done for the night.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Janet: "For a few days, at least. I need to..."

Text.LocalizedString: For a few days, at least. I need to figure out where this business district office is.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Player: "Let’s tentatively regroup this Frid..."

Text.LocalizedString: Let’s tentatively regroup this Friday, then? Hunter I know you’ve got some big exams this week.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Hunter: "I should have been studying this we..."

Text.LocalizedString: I should have been studying this weekend…

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Janet: "Sounds like a plan, [Act1Variables...."

Text.LocalizedString: Sounds like a plan, [Act1Variables.player].

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Hunter: "Yeah… Friday works."

Text.LocalizedString: Yeah… Friday works.

DialogueFragment.DisplayName: Player: "I’ll see you then."

Text.LocalizedString: I’ll see you then.

Text.LocalizedString: *With that, my friends depart, and I collapse onto my bed, exhausted. This weekend was rough, and I know next weekend will be even worse.*
